			<text>The WonderSwan is a handheld game console released in Japan by Bandai. Powered by a 16-bit central processing unit, the WonderSwan took advantage of a low price point and long battery life in comparison to its competition, Game Boy Color and Neo Geo Pocket Color.</text>
